	<div id="p110147" class="post row-fluid even">
	
		<div class="postbody span9">
			

			<div class="author">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=22978&amp;sid=a8a07dc8ca935fab95dcf953e3afa0ec">scape</a></strong> &raquo; Wed Jun 27, 2012 2:38 pm </div>

			

			<div class="content">have you made any changes to interfaces file?<br /><span style="font-style: italic">nano /etc/network/interfaces should appear as so:<br /># Used by ifup(8) and ifdown(8). See the interfaces(5) manpage or<br /># /usr/share/doc/ifupdown/examples for more information.<br /><br />auto lo<br /><br />iface lo inet loopback<br />iface eth0 inet dhcp<br /></span><br /><br />also consider trying: sudo ifup eth0 to get the adapter back up and hunting for dhcp.<br /><br />before all of this, plug your laptop in to the ethernet cable and make sure it's ethernet adapter is getting a connection and IP.</div>

			

		</div>

		
